  6. Deployment Workflow
  Based on the structure:
   1. Build: Azure Pipelines triggers a build and creates a Docker Image.
   2. Registry: The image is pushed to a container registry.
   3. Deploy: The files in the k8s/ folder are used to deploy the image to Alibaba Cloud Kubernetes.
   4. Routing: Nginx (configured in k8s/nginx/) acts as a reverse proxy/load balancer.


  7. Quick Start for Support/Troubleshooting
  If you have Docker Desktop installed, the fastest way to see the application running is to execute the following
  command in the root directory:
   1 docker-compose up --build
  This will automatically set up the website, the database, and the Nginx proxy in a unified environment. You can then
  access the site via localhost (port 80 or as specified in the compose file).

